Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveThe President, Major General Muhammadu Buhari (retd.), on Friday, met with ministers who were resigning to pursue their political ambitions.
The ministers include Minister of Petroleum, Timipre Sylva, Minister of Labour & Employment, Chris Ngige, Minister of State Mines & Steel, Uche Ogah, Minister of Justice, Abubakar Malami, Minister of Transportation, Rotimi Amaechi, Minister of Niger Delta, Godswill Akpabio, Minister of Science Technology, Ogbonnaya Onu, Minister of Women Affairs, Pauline Tallen, and Minister of State, Niger Delta, Tayo Alasoadura.
  
